// Provider hints (JSON5). OpenClaw discovers many providers automatically when auth env vars exist.
// Default template: Gemini developer API (provider google) — set GEMINI_API_KEY (or GSM + fetch-secrets-gsm.sh).
// Slow tools / Telegram: raise timeout — GEMINI_PROVIDER_TIMEOUT_SECONDS in .env or merge into openclaw.json:
//   models: { providers: { google: { timeoutSeconds: 180 } } }
// Optional Vertex (google-vertex): ADC from VM attached service account; set GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT / GOOGLE_CLOUD_LOCATION.
// See: https://docs.openclaw.ai/concepts/model-providers
{
  // Optional OpenAI fallback: set OPENAI_API_KEY in .env, then add failover in OpenClaw config
  // when you enable model failover (see upstream model-failover docs).
